{
  "texts": [
    "Currently, the most significant species raised for this purpose are the BSFL.",
    "The larvae must be transported and stored in a stable manner following production to prevent degradation.",
    "Both fermentation and vacuum packaging technology are viable stabilization options (Van Campenhout et al., 2021).",
    "The logistic chain includes stabilization, storage, and transportation in addition to the creation of larvae.",
    "A good preservation technique to pursue for the storage and transportation of BSFL is not thought to be vacuum packaging (Van Campenhout et al., 2021)."
  ]
}